description:
Males of this species are nearest *L. ochraceus* in general appearance but structurally nearer *L. dissimulans* by
(a) thorax uniformly pale to dark, marked black, or dark markings irregular with at most slight bronze sheen;
(b) inner border of cerci at least with prominent basal tooth;
(c) paraprocts blunt, without apical process.

However, differs by
(1) Pt more elongate, 1.5-2.0 mm;
(2) basal tooth on inner border of cerci sharp;
(3) paraprocts not extending beyond its tip, and constricted - creating a distinct apical knob.
